Flower Ordering Flow
Tanvir Raju
The product:
A website where user can order various types of
categorized flowers through an easy to experience
ordering flow for upcoming events.
Project overview
Project duration:
5/1/2023-Current
The problem:
Ordering various types of flowers for
appropriate events through an easy to user
experience.
Project overview
The goal:
Develop an easy to user experience ordering
flow so that the users can order flowers
various types of events.
My role:
UX designer, UX researcher, etc.

User research: summary
I have conducted various moderate and un-moderate researches on how to improve the flower
ordering flow ux. The research interviews included various range of users who love to browse and
select the specific flowers based on needs. They all tend to expect the flower ordering flow to be
more user simple, friendly and easier to use.
User research: pain points

Takeaways
Next steps
Going forward
Takeaways
Impact:
Users shared that the app made flower
ordering flow seem like something they could
actually help simplify. One quote from peer
feedback was that the flower ordering flow
needs to simplified as soon as possible.
What I learned:
I learned that even though the problem I was
trying to solve was a big one, diligently going
through each step of the design process and
aligning with specific user needs helped me
come up with solutions that were both feasible
and useful.
Next steps
Conduct research on how
successful the app is in
reaching the goal to
simplify flower ordering
flow.
Add more educational
resources for users to
learn about flower
ordering.
Provide incentives and
rewards to users for
successfully completed
flower ordering process.
